{
  "stem": "1799.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Matter of fact, my mother took a train to London to the-- you know, there's a train that goes to London by way of a ferry from France to London, which is now the tunnel.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I saw her in that train before she went on that ferry, in-- when was it-- in very end of 1945.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's the first time I'd seen my mother since 1939.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So here, I was a child in '39, not even 14.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And now in '45, I was 19.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the difference of five years or so made me-- I was a man, and I left as a child.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was-- she might not have recognized me, but she did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was a rather unusual meeting.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was just the two of us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew what train she would be on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was later in 1945.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Subsequently, I went to visit her and my sister in-- in London.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was no one to-- to help the-- it was just she and I, instead of maybe having someone say, here, Jerry, you know, lead me on, and-- and have my mother have somebody there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was unusual in that sense, and that we had to find each other.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother was full of emotion, as I was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "By then, I learned also, as I had before, that my father was, you know, not among the living.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father had been caught during a-- an arrest period in southern France in, sometime in 1943, and had the bad luck of having on him both his real and false papers.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
